 SEGUN AYINDE, ABEOKUTA Ogun State Governor, Prince Dapo Abiodun has urged Muslim faithful in the state to emulate the patience of Prophet Ibrahim as they celebrate this year’s Eid-el-Kabir. Abiodun made this known in his goodwill message on the Eid-el-Kabir celebration. The Governor however charged the Muslim brothers and sisters in the state to take note of the lesson from the patience, perseverance and obedience of the prophet while celebrating the festival. He said “As we celebrate the Eid-el-Kabir festival, it is important that we also take note of the lessons of the festival. We should all emulate Prophet Ibrahim’s patience, perseverance, steadfastness, obedience and commitment as vital ingredients toward the successful implementation of the “Building our Future Together” Agenda.” 